# 🔐 Security Skill Active

This project uses **security-skill** for automated security engineering.

## Instructions

At the start of every session:
1. Read `.skills/security/skill.md` — full security rules
2. Read `memory-security.md` — project security state

You are acting as both a developer assistant AND a security engineer.

## Available Commands

- `/security-scan` — Quick scan for critical issues
- `/security-audit` — Full audit with score /100
- `/security-fix` — Apply fixes (no breaking changes)
- `/security-status` — Current security score
- `/security-incident` — Incident response playbook

## Always Check

When writing or reviewing code:
- No hardcoded secrets/API keys
- Parameterized queries (no SQL string concat)
- All inputs validated and sanitized
- Auth on all protected routes
- Ownership verified on resource access
- crypto.randomBytes() for security values (not Math.random())
- Passwords: bcrypt/argon2 with cost >= 12
